DESCRIPTION
===========
The script provide the utlity to retrieve tweets using the tweets APIs, store tweets in local JSON file (tinydb format), and performing sentiment calculation

OPTIONS
=======
--verbose
    Turn on logging

--log-level, --log_level
    Specify the verbose level.  By default, log level is INFO

--log-config,--log_config
    Specify the logging configuration file

--db
    Specific the location of tweet database.  By default, it is store in "../data/tweets.json"

--oauth
    Specify the file contains OAuth Information.  By default, OAuth Information is stored in "oauth.json"

--parameter-file, --parameter_file
    Specific the file contains the script parameters.  By default, the list of query string is stored in "parameters.json"

--action
    Specific the action for the script.  The follow options are supported:
        - GET
        - APPEND
        - ANALYZE

--max-result, --max_result,
    Define the max number of records to retieve from Twitter API.  By default, the value is 100

--out
  Specify the file name for sentiment result.  By default, the value is "../data/tweet_sentiment_export.json"

PROCEDURE
=========
1) Regularly, run the script with APPEND action to add new tweets in the database
> python3 ./TweetSentiment.py --action=APPEND

2) To calculate sentiment for each tweet, run the script with ANALYZE action
> python3 ./TweetSentiment.py --action=ANALYZE
